From: Marcin FM <marcin@lgic.pl>
Subject: [PATCH] Version PDFium component library SONAMEs

Fedora requires shared libraries in the system library directory to have
versioned SONAMEs.  Use the Chromium compatibility major for PDFium and its
private Abseil and ICU components; the development package supplies only the
unversioned libpdfium linker symlink.

--- a/BUILD.gn
+++ b/BUILD.gn
@@ -227,0 +228 @@ component("pdfium") {
+  output_extension = "so.146"
--- a/third_party/abseil-cpp/BUILD.gn
+++ b/third_party/abseil-cpp/BUILD.gn
@@ -21,0 +22 @@ component("absl") {
+  output_extension = "so.146"
--- a/third_party/icu/BUILD.gn
+++ b/third_party/icu/BUILD.gn
@@ -399,0 +400 @@ generate_icuuc("icuuc_private") {
+  output_extension = "so.146"
